Requirements
------------
* python-django
* python-pylast

* A LastFM account and a LastFM API account (http://www.last.fm/api/account)

Install
-------
* $ git clone git://github.com/nikolaik/oliver_screen.git
* Rename and edit settings-sample.py to suit your needs.
* Make static files under oliver_screen/oliver_screen/static available with your webserver of choice.
* Set MEDIA_URL to the URL where static files are served.
* Set TEMPLATE_DIRS
* Set LASTFM_APIKEY and LASTFM_API_SECRET
* If using mod_wsgi under Apache, first rename and edit django-sample.wsgi. Then setup a WSGIAlias in your apache config pointing to the .wsgi-file.
* $ python manage.py syncdb (creating an admin user)
* Make sure the files have correct permission.
* Goto /admin and login with the admin user and add a username to LastFMUser and make active.
* Setup your music player (f.ex Spotify) to scrobble to that account.
* Goto / and you should be set :=)
